review_blob: Very dark with a thin tan head. Smells like a combination of smoke and red wine. Fruit and wood flavors come through. Gets better as you continue to drink it.
One of the more complex stouts, notes of roasted coffee, honey, and burbon. Has some burn for a stout. If this wasnt $30 a pint and didnt smell like piss it would be near the top of my list.
beer_name: FiftyFifty Imperial Eclipse Stout - Elijah Craig 12 Year Barrel
